    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="685"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d685">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Japan)/10–748</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Assistant Secretary of State for Occupied
                        Areas</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Saltzman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the United States Representative on the Far
                        Eastern Commission</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McCoy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-07">October 7,
                            1948</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Subject: Instructions on Compromise Language for paragraph 1 C
                    of <gloss target="#t_FEC1">FEC</gloss> 298/8.</p>
                <p>This will confirm the oral authorization given to Mr. Barnett<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d685fn1">Robert W. Barnett, member of the U.S. delegation to the Far
                        Eastern Commission.</note> to accept the compromise language for this
                    paragraph suggested by the United Kingdom as follows, or closely comparable
                    language to the same effect: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The specific travel authorized herein should be restricted to that
                            deemed essential to meet Japan’s peaceful needs as defined by the <gloss
                                target="#t_FEC1">FEC</gloss> and the number of Japanese commercial
                            representatives permitted to travel abroad should be similarly
                                restricted.”<note n="2" xml:id="d685fn2">For text as passed by the
                                    <gloss target="#t_FEC1">FEC</gloss> on October 21, see <hi
                                    rend="italic">The Far Eastern Commission</hi>, 2d report, p.
                                36.</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles</hi> E. <hi rend="smallcaps">Saltzman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
